{"info": {"address1": "126 East Lincoln Avenue", "city": "Rahway", "state": "NJ", "zip": "07065", "country": "United States", "phone": "908 740 4000", "website": "https://www.merck.com", "industry": "Drug Manufacturers - General", "industryKey": "drug-manufacturers-general", "industryDisp": "Drug Manufacturers - General", "sector": "Healthcare", "sectorKey": "healthcare", "sectorDisp": "Healthcare", "longBusinessSummary": "Merck & Co., Inc. operates as a healthcare company worldwide. It offers human health pharmaceutical for various areas under the Keytruda, Keytruda Qlex, Welireg, Gardasil, ProQuad, M-M-R II, Varivax, Vaxneuvance, Capvaxive, RotaTeq, Pneumovax 23, Bridion, Prevymis, Dificid, Zerbaxa, Winrevair, Adempas/ Verquvo, Ohtuvayre, Lagevrio, Isentress/Isentress HD, Delstrigo, Pifeltro, Belsomra, Januvia, and Janumet brands. The company also provides veterinary pharmaceuticals, vaccines and health management solutions and services, such as livestock products under the Nuflor, Bovilis/Vista, Bovilis Cryptium, Banamine, Estrumate, Matrix, Resflor, Zuprevo, Revalor, Safe-Guard, M+Pac, Porcilis, Circumvent, Nobilis/Innovax, Paracox and Coccivac, Exzolt, Slice, Imvixa, Clynav, Aquavac/Norvax, Aquaflor, Flexolt brands; Allflex Livestock Intelligence solutions; and companion animal products under the Bravecto One-Month, Bravecto Injectable/Quantum, Bravecto TriUNO, Bravecto Plus, Sentinel Spectrum, Sentinel Flavor Tabs, Numelvi, Optimmune, Nobivac NXT, GilvetMab, Otomax, Mometamax, Mometamax Ultra, Posatex, Caninsulin/Vetsulin, Panacur, Safeguard, Regumate, Prestige, Scalibor/Exspot, Sure Petcare, and Home Again brands. It has development and commercialization agreement for three of Daiichi Sankyo's deruxtecan ADC candidates; AstraZeneca PLC to co-development and co-commercialize AstraZeneca's Lynparza products for multiple cancer types; licensed to develop, manufacture and commercialize LM-299, a novel investigational PD-1/VEGF bispecific antibody from LaNova; and collaboration agreement with Eisai Co., Ltd., Bayer AG, and Ridgeback Biotherapeutics LP, as well Moderna, Inc. Merck & Co., Inc. has strategic collaboration with Infinimmune, Inc. to discover and develop antibodies against multiple therapeutic targets. The company was founded in 1891 and is headquartered in Rahway, New Jersey.", "fullTimeEmployees": 73000, "companyOfficers": [{"maxAge": 1, "name": "Mr. Robert M. Davis J.D.", "age": 58, "title": "Chairman, President & CEO", "yearBorn": 1967, "fiscalYear": 2025, "totalPay": 4629860, "exercisedValue": 0, "unexercisedValue": 12892902}, {"maxAge": 1, "name": "Ms. Caroline A. Litchfield", "age": 56, "title": "Executive VP & CFO", "yearBorn": 1969, "fiscalYear": 2025, "totalPay": 2400632, "exercisedValue": 0, "unexercisedValue": 8697230}, {"maxAge": 1, "name": "Mr. Dalton E. Smart III", "age": 58, "title": "Senior VP of Finance, Principal Accounting Officer & Global Controller", "yearBorn": 1967, "fiscalYear": 2025, "exercisedValue": 0, "unexercisedValue": 0}, {"maxAge": 1, "name": "Mr. David Michael Williams", "age": 56, "title": "Executive VP and Chief Information & Digital Officer", "yearBorn": 1969, "fiscalYear": 2025, "exercisedValue": 0, "unexercisedValue": 0}, {"maxAge": 1, "name": "Mr. Peter  Dannenbaum", "title": "Vice President of Investor Relations", "fiscalYear": 2025, "exercisedValue": 0, "unexercisedValue": 0}, {"maxAge": 1, "name": "Mr. Johannes J. Oosthuizen", "age": 57, "title": "Executive VP and President of Oncology & MSD International", "yearBorn": 1968, "fiscalYear": 2025, "exercisedValue": 0, "unexercisedValue": 0}, {"maxAge": 1, "name": "Dr. Eric H. Rubin M.D.", "age": 65, "title": "Senior Vice President of Global Clinical Oncology & Early-stage Oncology", "yearBorn": 1960, "fiscalYear": 2025, "exercisedValue": 0, "unexercisedValue": 0}, {"maxAge": 1, "name": "Dr. Eliav  Barr M.D.", "age": 60, "title": "Chief Medical Officer & Head of Global Clinical Development of Merck Research Laboratories", "ye